HTTPCallback.Name: HTTPCallback
HTTPCallback.Description: Performs an HTTP request at the end of a pipeline run.

SnapshotParquet.Name: SnapshotParquet
SnapshotParquet.Description:
A batch source that reads from a corresponding SnapshotParquet sink.
The source will only read the most recent snapshot written to the sink.

SSH.Name: SSH
SSH.Description: Establishes an SSH connection with remote machine to execute command on that machine.

Cube.Name: Cube
Cube.Description: Batch sink that writes data to a Cube dataset.

Table.Name: Table
Table.Description:
Outputs the entire contents of a CDAP Table each batch interval. The Table contents will be refreshed
at configurable intervals.

SnapshotAvro.Name: SnapshotAvro
SnapshotAvro.Description:
A batch sink for a PartitionedFileSet that writes snapshots of data as a new
partition. Data is written in Avro format. A corresponding SnapshotAvro source
can be used to read only the most recently written snapshot.

Email.Name: Email
Email.Description: Sends an email at the end of a pipeline run.

FTP.Name: FTP
FTP.Description:
Batch source for an FTP or SFTP source. Prefix of the path ('ftp://...' or 'sftp://...') determines the source server
type, either FTP or SFTP.

TMS.Name: TMS
TMS.Description:
Publishes alerts to the CDAP Transactional Messaging System (TMS) as json objects. The plugin
allows you to specify the topic and namespace to publish to, as well as a rate limit for the
maximum number of alerts to publish per second.

XMLReader.Name: XMLReader
XMLReader.Description: The XML Reader plugin is a source plugin that allows users to read XML files stored on HDFS.

HDFSMove.Name: HDFSMove
HDFSMove.Description: Moves a file or files within an HDFS cluster.

LogParser.Name: LogParser
LogParser.Description:
Parses logs from any input source for relevant information such as URI, IP,
browser, device, HTTP status code, and timestamp.

JavaScript.Name: JavaScript
JavaScript.Description:
Executes user-provided JavaScript that transforms one record into zero or more records.
Input records are converted into JSON objects which can be directly accessed in
JavaScript. The transform expects to receive a JSON object as input, which it can
process and emit zero or more records or emit error using the provided emitter object.

KVTable.Name: KVTable
KVTable.Description:
Reads the entire contents of a KeyValueTable, outputting records with a 'key' field and a
'value' field. Both fields are of type bytes.

HDFSDelete.Name: HDFSDelete
HDFSDelete.Description: Deletes a file or files within an HDFS cluster.

RowDenormalizer.Name: RowDenormalizer
RowDenormalizer.Description: Converts raw data into denormalized data based on a key column. User is able to specify the list of fields that should be used in the denormalized record, with an option to use an alias for the output field name. For example, 'ADDRESS' in the input is mapped to 'addr' in the output schema.

File.Name: File
File.Description:
File streaming source. Watches a directory and streams file contents of any new files added to the directory.
Files must be atomically moved or renamed.

Distinct.Name: Distinct
Distinct.Description:
De-duplicates input records so that all output records are distinct.
Can optionally take a list of fields, which will project out all other fields and perform a distinct on just those fields.

PythonEvaluator.Name: PythonEvaluator
PythonEvaluator.Description:
Executes user-provided python code that transforms one record into zero or more records.
Each input record is converted into a dictionary which can be directly accessed in
python. The transform expects to receive a dictionary as input, which it can
process and emit zero or more transformed dictionaries, or emit an error dictionary using the provided emitter object.

Window.Name: Window
Window.Description: The Window plugin is used to window a part of a streaming pipeline.

ErrorCollector.Name: ErrorCollector
ErrorCollector.Description:
The ErrorCollector plugin takes errors emitted from the previous stage and flattens them by adding
the error message, code, and stage to the record and outputting the result.

StructuredRecordToGenericRecord.Name: StructuredRecordToGenericRecord
StructuredRecordToGenericRecord.Description: Transforms a StructuredRecord into an Avro GenericRecord.

SnapshotText.Name: SnapshotText
SnapshotText.Description:
A batch sink for a PartitionedFileSet that writes snapshots of data as a new
partition. Data is written in Text format.

WindowsShareCopy.Name: WindowsShareCopy
WindowsShareCopy.Description: Copies a file or files on a Microsoft Windows share to an HDFS directory.

Validator.Name: Validator
Validator.Description:
Validates a record, writing to an error dataset if the record is invalid.
Otherwise it passes the record on to the next stage.

Excel.Name: Excel
Excel.Description: The Excel plugin provides user the ability to read data from one or more Excel file(s).

Projection.Name: Projection
Projection.Description:
The Projection transform lets you drop, keep, rename, and cast fields to a different type.
Fields are first dropped based on the drop or keep field, then cast, then renamed.

MLPredictor.Name: MLPredictor
MLPredictor.Description:
Uses a model trained by the ModelTrainer plugin to add a prediction field to incoming records.
The same features used to train the model must be present in each input record, but input records can also
contain additional non-feature fields. If the trained model uses categorical features,
and if the record being predicted contains new categories, that record will be dropped.
For example, suppose categorical feature 'city' was used to train a model that predicts housing prices.
If an incoming record has 'New York' as the city, but 'New York' was not in the training set,
that record will be dropped.

S3.Name: S3
S3.Description: Batch source to use Amazon S3 as a Source.

Wrangler.Name: Wrangler
Wrangler.Description:
This plugin applies data transformation directives on your data records. The directives
are generated either through an interactive user interface or by manual entry into the
plugin.

XMLParser.Name: XMLParser
XMLParser.Description:
The XML Parser Transform uses XPath to extract fields from a complex XML event. This plugin should generally be used
in conjunction with the XML Reader Batch Source. The XML Reader will provide individual events to the XML Parser,
which will be responsible for extracting fields from the events and mapping them to the output schema.

XMLMultiParser.Name: XMLMultiParser
XMLMultiParser.Description:
The XML Multi Parser Transform uses XPath to extract fields from an XML document. It will generate records from
the children of the element specified by the XPath. If there is some error parsing the document or building the record,
the problematic input record will be dropped.

UnionSplitter.Name: UnionSplitter
UnionSplitter.Description: The union splitter is used to split data by a union schema, so that type specific logic can be done downstream.

CloneRecord.Name: CloneRecord
CloneRecord.Description:
Makes a copy of every input record received for a configured number of times on the output. 
This transform does not change any record fields or types. It's an identity transform.

ValueMapper.Name: ValueMapper
ValueMapper.Description:
Value Mapper is a transform plugin that maps string values of a field in the input record
to a mapping value using a mapping dataset.

XMLToJSON.Name: XMLToJSON
XMLToJSON.Description:
Accepts a field that contains a properly-formatted XML string and 
outputs a properly-formatted JSON string version of the data. This is 
meant to be used with the Javascript transform for the parsing of 
complex XML documents into parts. Once the XML is a JSON string, you 
can convert it into a Javascript object using:

Decryptor.Name: Decryptor
Decryptor.Description:
Decrypts one or more fields in input records using a keystore 
that must be present on all nodes of the cluster.

Encryptor.Name: Encryptor
Encryptor.Description:
Encrypts one or more fields in input records using a java keystore 
that must be present on all nodes of the cluster.

Normalize.Name: Normalize
Normalize.Description:
Normalize is a transform plugin that breaks one source row into multiple target rows.
Attributes stored in the columns of a table or a file may need to be broken into multiple
records: for example, one record per column attribute. In general, the plugin allows the
conversion of columns to rows.

Compressor.Name: Compressor
Compressor.Description:
Compresses configured fields. Multiple fields can be specified to be compressed using different compression algorithms.
Plugin supports SNAPPY, ZIP, and GZIP types of compression of fields.

JSONParser.Name: JSONParser
JSONParser.Description:
Parses an input JSON event into a record. The input JSON event could be either a map of
string fields to values or it could be a complex nested JSON structure. The plugin allows you
to express JSON paths for extracting fields from complex nested input JSON.

Twitter.Name: Twitter
Twitter.Description: Samples tweets in real-time through Spark streaming. Output records will have this schema:

Conditional.Name: Conditional
Conditional.Description:
A control flow plugin that allows conditional execution within
pipelines. The conditions are specified as expressions and the
variables could include values specified as runtime arguments of
the pipeline, token from plugins prior to the condition and global
that includes global information about pipeline like stage, pipeline,
logical start time and plugin.

KafkaAlerts.Name: KafkaAlerts
KafkaAlerts.Description:
Kafka Alert Publisher that allows you to publish alerts to kafka as json objects.
The plugin internally uses kafka producer apis to publish alerts. 
The plugin allows to specify kafka topic to use for publishing and other additional
kafka producer properties. This plugin uses kafka 0.10.2 java apis.

BigQueryTable.Name: BigQueryTable
BigQueryTable.Description:
This plugins exports a bigquery table as sink to be ingested into the processing pipeline.
Plugin requires a service account to access the bigquery table. In order to configure
the service account visit https://cloud.google.com. Make sure you provide right permissions
to service account for accessing BigQuery API.

GCSBucketCreate.Name: GCSBucketCreate
GCSBucketCreate.Description: This plugin is used for creating directories on Google Cloud Storage (GCS).

GCS.Name: GCS
GCS.Description:
This plugin writes records to one or more files in a directory on Google Cloud Storage.
Files can be written in various formats such as csv, avro, parquet, and json.

Spanner.Name: Spanner
Spanner.Description:
This source reads from a Google Cloud Spanner table.
Cloud Spanner is a fully managed, mission-critical, relational database service that offers transactional
consistency at global scale, schemas, SQL (ANSI 2011 with extensions),
and automatic, synchronous replication for high availability.

GCSBucketDelete.Name: GCSBucketDelete
GCSBucketDelete.Description: This plugin is used for deleting directories on Google Cloud Storage (GCS).

SpeechToText.Name: SpeechToText
SpeechToText.Description: This plugin converts audio files to text by using Google Cloud Speech-to-Text.

Database.Name: Database
Database.Description: Writes records to a database table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

DatabaseQuery.Name: DatabaseQuery
DatabaseQuery.Description:
Runs a database query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

HBase.Name: HBase
HBase.Description:
Batch source that reads from a column family in an HBase table.
This source differs from the Table source in that it does not use a CDAP dataset,
but reads directly from HBase.

S3FileMetadataSource.Name: S3FileMetadataSource
S3FileMetadataSource.Description: The S3 File Metadata plugin is a source plugin that allows users to read file metadata from an S3 Filesystem.

FileMetadataSource.Name: FileMetadataSource
FileMetadataSource.Description: The File Metadata plugin is a source plugin that allows users to read file metadata from a local HDFS or a local filesystem.

FileCopySink.Name: FileCopySink
FileCopySink.Description: The File Copy plugin is a sink plugin that takes file metadata records as inputs and copies the files into the local HDFS or the local filesystem.

S3FileCopySink.Name: S3FileCopySink
S3FileCopySink.Description: The S3 File Copy plugin is a sink plugin that takes file metadata records as inputs and copies the files into an Amazon S3 filesystem.

OracleExport.Name: OracleExport
OracleExport.Description:
A Hydrator Action plugin to efficiently export data from Oracle to HDFS or local file system. The plugin uses
Oracle's command line tools to export data. The data exported from this tool can then be used in Hydrator pipelines.

AzureDecompress.Name: AzureDecompress
AzureDecompress.Description: Azure decompress Action plugin decompress gz files from a container on Azure Storage Blob service into another container.

AzureDelete.Name: AzureDelete
AzureDelete.Description: Azure Delete Action plugin deletes a container on Azure Storage Blob service.

VerticaBulkExportAction.Name: VerticaBulkExportAction
VerticaBulkExportAction.Description: Bulk exports data in a vertica table into a file.

Trash.Name: Trash
Trash.Description:
Trash consumes all the records on the input and eats them all,
means no output is generated or no output is stored anywhere.

ArgumentSetter.Name: ArgumentSetter
ArgumentSetter.Description:
Performs an HTTP request some endpoint to get a driver specification. Based on the spec,
it will make another call to a nebula endpoint to get data about the dataset, which it will
use to set 'input.path', 'input.properties', 'directives', and 'output.schema' arguments
that can be used later on in the pipeline through macros.

DataFactoryDriver.Name: DataFactoryDriver
DataFactoryDriver.Description:
Performs an HTTP request some endpoint to get a driver specification. Based on the spec,
it will make another call to a nebula endpoint to get data about the dataset, which it will
use to set 'input.path', 'input.properties', 'directives', and 'output.schema' arguments
that can be used later on in the pipeline through macros.

AmazonS3Client.Name: AmazonS3Client
AmazonS3Client.Description: The Amazon S3 Client Action is used to work with S3 buckets and objects before or after the execution of a pipeline.

Kudu.Name: Kudu
Kudu.Description: CDAP Plugin for reading data from Apache Kudu table.

DataProfiler.Name: DataProfiler
DataProfiler.Description:
Calculates statistics for each input field.
For every field, a total count and null count will be calculated.
For numeric fields, min, max, mean, stddev, zero count, positive count, and negative count will be calculated.
For string fields, min length, max length, mean length, and empty count will be calculated.
For boolean fields, true and false counts will be calculated.
When calculating means, only non-null values are considered.

AzureBlobStore.Name: AzureBlobStore
AzureBlobStore.Description: Batch source to use Microsoft Azure Blob Storage as a source.

FileAppender.Name: FileAppender
FileAppender.Description:
Writes to a CDAP FileSet in text format. HDFS append must be enabled for this to work.
One line is written for each record sent to the sink.
All record fields are joined using a configurable separator.
Each time a batch is written, the sink will examine all existing files in the output directory.
If there are any files that are smaller in size than the size threshold, or more recent than
the age threshold, new data will be appended to those files instead of written to new files.

Run.Name: Run
Run.Description:
Runs an executable binary which is installed and available on the local filesystem of the Hadoop nodes. Run transform
plugin allows the user to read the structured record as input and returns the output record, to be further processed
downstream in the pipeline.

DecisionTreePredictor.Name: DecisionTreePredictor
DecisionTreePredictor.Description: Loads a Decision Tree Regression model from a FileSet and uses it to label the records based on the predicted values.

DecisionTreeTrainer.Name: DecisionTreeTrainer
DecisionTreeTrainer.Description: Trains a regression model based upon a particular label and features of a record. Saves this model to a FileSet.

TopN.Name: TopN
TopN.Description: Top-N returns the top "n" records from the input set, based on the criteria specified in the plugin configuration.

S3ToRedshift.Name: S3ToRedshift
S3ToRedshift.Description: S3ToRedshift Action that will load the data from AWS S3 bucket into the AWS Redshift table.

KinesisSource.Name: KinesisSource
KinesisSource.Description: Spark streaming source that reads from AWS Kinesis streams.

DateTransform.Name: DateTransform
DateTransform.Description: This transform takes a date in either a unix timestamp or a string, and converts it to a formatted string. (Macro-enabled)

FailPipeline.Name: FailPipeline
FailPipeline.Description:
Batch Sink is used to fail the running pipeline when any of the record flows to this sink on receiving
the first record itself.

ADLSBatchSink.Name: ADLSBatchSink
ADLSBatchSink.Description: Azure Data Lake Store Batch Sink writes data to Azure Data Lake Store directory in avro, orc or text format.

ADLSDelete.Name: ADLSDelete
ADLSDelete.Description: Deletes a file or files within ADLS file system.

AzureDataLakeStore.Name: AzureDataLakeStore
AzureDataLakeStore.Description:
Azure Data Lake Store Batch Source reads data from Azure Data Lake Store files and converts it into 
StructuredRecord.

AzureEventHub.Name: AzureEventHub
AzureEventHub.Description:
Azure Event Hub streaming source. Emits a record with the schema specified by the user. If no schema
is specified, it will emit a record with 'message'(bytes).

Elasticsearch.Name: Elasticsearch
Elasticsearch.Description:
Takes the Structured Record from the input source and converts it to a JSON string, then indexes it in
Elasticsearch using the index, type, and idField specified by the user. The Elasticsearch server should
be running prior to creating the application.

OrientDB.Name: OrientDB
OrientDB.Description: Writes data to an OrientDB database.

HDFSFileMerge.Name: HDFSFileMerge
HDFSFileMerge.Description: Merges small files within an HDFS cluster.

Sampling.Name: Sampling
Sampling.Description:
Sampling a large dataset flowing through this plugin to pull random records. Supports two types of sampling
i.e, Systematic Sampling and Reservoir Sampling.

S3Avro.Name: S3Avro
S3Avro.Description: A batch sink for writing to Amazon S3 in Avro format.

S3Parquet.Name: S3Parquet
S3Parquet.Description: A batch sink to write to S3 in Parquet format.

FTPCopy.Name: FTPCopy
FTPCopy.Description: Copy files from FTP server to the specified destination.

CDCDatabase.Name: CDCDatabase
CDCDatabase.Description: This plugin reads Change Data Capture (CDC) events from a Golden Gate Kafka topic.

CDCHBase.Name: CDCHBase
CDCHBase.Description:
This plugin takes input from a CDC source and writes the changes to HBase. 
It will write to the HBase instance running on the cluster.

CDCKudu.Name: CDCKudu
CDCKudu.Description: This plugin takes input from a CDC source and writes the changes to Kudu.

HTTP.Name: HTTP
HTTP.Description: Sink plugin to send the messages from the pipeline to an external http endpoint.

DynamicMultiFileset.Name: DynamicMultiFileset
DynamicMultiFileset.Description:
This plugin is normally used in conjunction with the MultiTableDatabase batch source to write records from multiple
databases into multiple filesets in text format. Each fileset it writes to will contain a single 'ingesttime' partition,
which will contain the logical start time of the pipeline run. The plugin expects that the filsets it needs to write
to will be set as pipeline arguments, where the key is 'multisink.[fileset]' and the value is the fileset schema.
Normally, you rely on the MultiTableDatabase source to set those pipeline arguments, but they can also be manually
set or set by an Action plugin in your pipeline. The sink will expect each record to contain a special split field
that will be used to determine which records are written to each fileset. For example, suppose the
the split field is 'tablename'. A record whose 'tablename' field is set to 'activity' will be written to the 'activity'
fileset.

MultiTableDatabase.Name: MultiTableDatabase
MultiTableDatabase.Description:
Reads from multiple tables within a database using JDBC. Often used in conjunction with the DynamicMultiFileset sink
to perform dumps from multiple tables to HDFS files in a single pipeline. The source will output a record for each
row in the tables it reads, with each record containing an additional field that holds the name of the table the
record came from. In addition, for each table that will be read, this plugin will set pipeline arguments where the
key is 'multisink.[tablename]' and the value is the schema of the table. This is to make it work with the
DynamicMultiFileset.

AddField.Name: AddField
AddField.Description:
Adds a new field to each record. The field value can either be a new UUID, or it can be set directly through
configuration. This transform is used when you want to add a unique id field to each record, or when you want
to tag each record with some constant value. For example, you may want to add the logical start time as a field
to each record.

MultiFieldAdder.Name: MultiFieldAdder
MultiFieldAdder.Description:
Multi Field Adder Transform allows you to add one or more fields to the output.
Each field specified has a name and the value. The value is currently set to
be of type string.

GCSParquet.Name: GCSParquet
GCSParquet.Description: A GCS sink to write records as AVRO records into Parquet files.

GCSAvro.Name: GCSAvro
GCSAvro.Description: A GCS sink to write records as AVRO records.

GCSText.Name: GCSText
GCSText.Description:
A GCS sink to write records as Comma, Tab, Pipe, CTRL+A separated or JSON
text files.

MapRDBJSON.Name: MapRDBJSON
MapRDBJSON.Description: MapR-DB JSON table sink is used to write the JSON documents to the MapR-DB table.

MapRStream.Name: MapRStream
MapRStream.Description: MapR streaming source. Reads events from MapR stream.

NaiveBayesClassifier.Name: NaiveBayesClassifier
NaiveBayesClassifier.Description: Loads a Naive Bayes model from a file of a FileSet dataset and uses it to classify records.

NaiveBayesTrainer.Name: NaiveBayesTrainer
NaiveBayesTrainer.Description:
Using a Naive Bayes algorithm, trains a model based upon a particular label and text field of a record.
Saves this model to a file in a FileSet dataset.

Repartitioner.Name: Repartitioner
Repartitioner.Description: This plugins re-partitions a Spark RDD.

ScalaSparkProgram.Name: ScalaSparkProgram
ScalaSparkProgram.Description: Executes user-provided Spark code in Scala.

PySparkProgram.Name: PySparkProgram
PySparkProgram.Description: Executes user-provided Spark code in Python.

ScalaSparkCompute.Name: ScalaSparkCompute
ScalaSparkCompute.Description:
Executes user-provided Spark code in Scala that transforms RDD to RDD with full
access to all Spark features.

ScalaSparkSink.Name: ScalaSparkSink
ScalaSparkSink.Description:
Executes user-provided Spark code in Scala that operates on an input RDD or Dataframe with full
access to all Spark features.

MQTT.Name: MQTT
MQTT.Description:
The MQTT Streaming Source allows you to subscribe to an MQTT broker in a streaming context. You
specify the topic to subscribe to as an MQTT client.

VerticaBulkImportAction.Name: VerticaBulkImportAction
VerticaBulkImportAction.Description: Vertica Bulk Import Action plugin gets executed after successful mapreduce or spark job. It reads all the files in a given directory and bulk imports contents of those files into vertica table.

DynamoDB.Name: DynamoDB
DynamoDB.Description:
DynamoDB Batch Source that will read the data items from AWS DynamoDB table and convert each item into the
StructuredRecord as per the schema specified by the user, that can be further processed downstream in the pipeline.
User can provide the query, to read the items from DynamoDB table.

MainframeReader.Name: MainframeReader
MainframeReader.Description: This is a source plugin that allows users to read and process mainframe files.

KinesisSink.Name: KinesisSink
KinesisSink.Description: Kinesis sink that outputs to a specified Amazon Kinesis Stream.

HTTPToHDFS.Name: HTTPToHDFS
HTTPToHDFS.Description: Action to fetch data from an external http endpoint and create a file in HDFS.

RecordSplitter.Name: RecordSplitter
RecordSplitter.Description: Given a field and a delimiter, emits one record for each split of the field.

FileContents.Name: FileContents
FileContents.Description:
This action plugin can be used to check if a file is empty or if the
contents of a file match a given pattern.

LogisticRegressionClassifier.Name: LogisticRegressionClassifier
LogisticRegressionClassifier.Description: Loads a Logistic Regression model from a file of a FileSet dataset and uses it to classify records.

LogisticRegressionTrainer.Name: LogisticRegressionTrainer
LogisticRegressionTrainer.Description: Trains a classification model based upon a particular label and features of a record. Saves this model to a FileSet.

FastFilter.Name: FastFilter
FastFilter.Description: Filters out messages based on a specified criteria.

CDCBigTable.Name: CDCBigTable
CDCBigTable.Description: This plugin takes input from a CDC source and writes the changes to Cloud Bigtable.
